Privacy Policy for Bnei Aliyah

Effective Date: May 14, 2025

At Bnei Aliyah, your privacy is important to us. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, and protect your information when you use our website.

1. What We Collect
- IP address
- Geolocation (city, region, country)
- Device/browser details (user agent)
- Referring website
- Timestamps for visit start and end
- Duration of your visit
- If logged in: associated user ID

2. Why We Collect This
We use this information to:
- Improve our services and user experience
- Understand visitor behavior and analytics
- Maintain security and prevent misuse

3. Data Retention
Data is stored securely and may be retained for analytical or security purposes. We do not sell or share data with third parties.

4. Cookies
We may use cookies to improve functionality or track session activity.

5. Your Rights
You may request deletion or access to your personal data by contacting:
mybs2323@gmail.com

6. Consent
By using our website, you consent to the terms of this Privacy Policy.

